  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Even the school nurse added her name to The List that first week, asking for a quieter corner to rest during her break.",
      "zh": "第一週，連學校護理師都把自己的名字加進了清單，申請一個安靜的角落在休息時間使用。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The new episode did not use Mr. Pan's name, but somehow, most of the school understood exactly who it was about.",
      "zh": "新一集沒有用潘老師的名字，但不知道為什麼，大部分同學都聽得出來這是在說誰。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Nobody said his name out loud, either. It became a kind of quiet agreement across the whole school.",
      "zh": "也沒有人把他的名字說出口，這變成整間學校一種默契的安靜協議。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Students Coco had never spoken to stopped her in the hallway just to say the episode had made them think.",
      "zh": "Coco 從沒說過話的學生，在走廊上攔住她，只是想說這一集讓他們想了很多。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One boy admitted he had never noticed the quiet kid who sat behind him all year.",
      "zh": "一個男生坦承，他整年都沒注意到坐在他後面那個安靜的同學。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A teacher asked Mr. Pan, half joking, if the school should build \"a Ten Minute Club\" of its own again.",
      "zh": "一位老師半開玩笑地問潘老師，學校是不是該重新辦一個「十分鐘社」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan didn't answer right away, but Coco noticed he wrote something down afterward.",
      "zh": "潘老師沒有馬上回答，但 Coco 注意到他後來寫了些什麼。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A week later, the school told everyone something new: any student could ask for a quiet space, a practice room, or a small kind of help, without needing a special reason.",
      "zh": "一星期後，學校告訴大家一件新事情：任何學生都可以申請安靜空間、練習室，或一點小小的幫助，不需要什麼特別的理由。"
    },
    {
      "en": "They called it, simply, \"The List.\" No long explanation, no long rules. Just a place to write down what you needed.",
      "zh": "他們就簡單地把它叫做「清單」，沒有長篇解釋，沒有一堆規則，只是一個寫下你需要什麼的地方。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That's it,\" Bernice said, reading the notice. \"That's basically Locker 113, but official.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 讀著告示說：「就是這個，這根本就是113號置物櫃，只是變成正式的了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Maybe that's how it should work,\" Coco said. \"Small things first. Rules later, if they're even needed.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「也許本來就該這樣，先有小小的事情，需要的話規則之後再說。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The Friday Box, meanwhile, kept receiving notes, faster than ever before.",
      "zh": "與此同時，Friday Box 收到紙條的速度，比以前任何時候都快。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Some were new mysteries. Some were simple thank-yous. A few were just single words: \"seen,\" \"helped,\" \"better.\"",
      "zh": "有些是新的謎團，有些只是簡單的謝謝，還有幾張只寫了一個字：「被看見」、「被幫助」、「變好了」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco started a new page in her notebook just for these short notes, separate from the cases.",
      "zh": "Coco 在筆記本裡開了新的一頁，專門放這些短短的紙條，跟案子分開放。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She didn't have a name for that page yet, but she had a feeling it might end up being the most important one.",
      "zh": "她還沒幫這一頁取名字，但她有種感覺，這一頁可能會是最重要的一頁。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One student asked The List for something simple: a clean, quiet place to change clothes before an after-school swim class.",
      "zh": "一個學生在清單上申請了一件很簡單的事：放學後上游泳課前，一個乾淨安靜的更衣空間。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Another asked for a warm place to wait during winter, since the school gate could be cold and windy in the morning.",
      "zh": "另一個學生申請一個冬天可以取暖的地方，因為早上校門口又冷又有風。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At the end-of-term assembly, the principal gave a short speech about the year.",
      "zh": "學期末的週會上，校長對這一年做了一段簡短的致詞。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Every student has the ability to notice something small and act on it,\" she said.",
      "zh": "她說：「每個學生都有能力去注意到一件小事，並且採取行動。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"This isn't about business, or about being popular. It's about paying attention.\"",
      "zh": "「這跟做生意無關，也跟受不受歡迎無關，這是關於用心去注意。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"You had the choice to look away from a strange clock, an empty locker, or a barking dog,\" she continued.",
      "zh": "她接著說：「你們原本可以選擇對一個奇怪的鐘、一個空的置物櫃，或一隻愛叫的狗視而不見。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Instead, you asked a question, and that experience changed how this whole school pays attention to itself.\"",
      "zh": "「但你們卻選擇去問問題，而這個經驗改變了整間學校關注彼此的方式。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "She thanked the podcast club for its interest in the school's daily life, calling it a useful example for younger students.",
      "zh": "她感謝這個 podcast 社團對校園日常生活的關注，稱讚它是給學弟妹的好榜樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I have no doubt,\" she added, \"that next year's students will carry on the same habit of asking good questions.\"",
      "zh": "她補充說：「我相信，明年的學生一定會延續這個問好問題的習慣。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The whole hall clapped, and for once, Bernice didn't make a joke about it.",
      "zh": "全場鼓掌，這一次，Bernice 沒有拿這件事開玩笑。"
    }
  ],
